## Animations

All animations use vanilla JS IntersectionObserver — no animation libraries. Existing:
- Hero: Dana Levi row progress animation (2/4 → 4/4)
- How It Works: Sequential step reveal with connecting line
- ROI: Count-up numbers on scroll
- WhatsApp Demo: Messages appear sequentially, status transitions
- Cards: 2px hover lift with border brightening

## Design Agents

Three specialized agent prompts are available in `.cursor/agents/`:

- **ui-designer.md** — Visual consistency, component quality, typography hierarchy, responsive design, accessibility. Use when working on component styling or layout.
- **ux-architect.md** — Information architecture, conversion path, content hierarchy, user flow. Use when restructuring pages or optimizing for conversions.
- **brand-guardian.md** — Brand voice, forbidden terms, naming conventions, visual brand compliance. Use when writing or reviewing copy.

Reference these agents when doing design/UX/copy work. They are tailored to this project's design system and brand rules.

## When editing

- Read the relevant `docs/` file before changing copy (e.g., docs/website/homepage.md for homepage)
- Keep the dark theme consistent — use Tailwind classes from the design system
- Hebrew text uses `font-hebrew` (Heebo) and `dir="rtl"`
- Test with `npm run dev` (localhost:4321)
